Tshwane Mayor Steve Mokgalapa will hear his fate today. The ANC has tabled a motion of no confidence against him. The party claims the executive mayor has underminded council resolutions for a month. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Tshwane mayor, Stevens Mokgalapa will face his first motion of no-confidence on Thursday. Mokgalapa was elected mayor in February after replacing Solly Msimanga. The ANC caucus will table the motion of no-confidence. READ: ANC withdraws motion of no-confidence against Mashaba The party says the mayor has undermined council resolutions for a month. Tshwane city manager, Moeketsi Mosola was granted an extension until 31 August but council resolved to appoint chief operations officer James Murphy as his replacement.